20/1/19
Fine and uneventful day. I walked over to Bde.H.Q. in the evening with Gorman and had afternoon tea there. No fresh news. Came back through the Woods over boggy paths which today are frozen hard. In the twilight the many lights of surrounding villages are twinkling. Mess was a merry meal by reason of fellows back from leave and the presence as guest of our old friend Col. (Dr) Simmonds. Cold and frosty night.